      "acceptanceCriteria": "All material and boundary-condition inputs documented with sources; stochastic variability characterised via probability distributions derived from measurement data.",
      "rationale": "Blood viscosity, impeller tip clearance, and inlet flow waveform were identified as the primary stochastic inputs. Probability distributions were fitted to measurement datasets (n ≥ 30 per parameter). A comprehensive Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification study propagated these distributions through the CFD model across 500 Latin-hypercube samples, yielding 95th-percentile bounds on the relative hemolysis index. All input distributions and sampling records are archived. This satisfies the MRL 2 model-inputs requirement."
